databases.description: Some example data for you to play around with as you embark on your Metabase journey.
databases.name: Sample Database
databases.caveats: You probably don't want to use this for your business-critical analyses, but hey, it's your world, we're just living in it.
databases.points_of_interest: You can find all sorts of different joinable tables ranging from products to people to reviews here.

tables.description: Confirmed Sample Company orders for a product, from a user.
tables.name: ORDERS

fields.description: This is a unique ID for the product. It is also called the “Invoice number” or “Confirmation number” in customer facing emails and screens.
fields.name: ID

fields.description: The id of the user who made this order. Note that in some cases where an order was created on behalf of a customer who phoned the order in, this might be the employee who handled the request.
fields.name: USER_ID

target.description: A unique identifier given to each user.
target.name: ID

fields.description: The product ID. This is an internal identifier for the product, NOT the SKU.
fields.name: PRODUCT_ID

target.description: The numerical product number. Only used internally. All external communication should use the title or EAN.
target.name: ID

fields.description: The raw, pre-tax cost of the order. Note that this might be different in the future from the product price due to promotions, credits, etc.
fields.name: SUBTOTAL

fields.description: This is the amount of local and federal taxes that are collected on the purchase. Note that other governmental fees on some products are not included here, but instead are accounted for in the subtotal.
fields.name: TAX

fields.description: The total billed amount.
fields.name: TOTAL

fields.description: Discount amount.
fields.name: DISCOUNT

fields.description: The date and time an order was submitted.
fields.name: CREATED_AT

fields.description: Number of products bought.
fields.name: QUANTITY

tables.caveats: You can join this on the Products and Orders table using the ID fields. Discount is left null if not applicable.

tables.description: Information on the user accounts registered with Sample Company.
tables.name: PEOPLE

fields.description: A unique identifier given to each user.
fields.name: ID

fields.description: The street address of the account’s billing address
fields.name: ADDRESS

fields.description: The contact email for the account.
fields.name: EMAIL

fields.description: This is the salted password of the user. It should not be visible
fields.name: PASSWORD

fields.description: The name of the user who owns an account
fields.name: NAME

fields.description: The city of the account’s billing address
fields.name: CITY

fields.description: This is the longitude of the user on sign-up. It might be updated in the future to the last seen location.
fields.name: LONGITUDE

fields.description: The state or province of the account’s billing address
fields.name: STATE

fields.description: The channel through which we acquired this user. Valid values include: Affiliate, Facebook, Google, Organic and Twitter
fields.name: SOURCE

fields.description: The date of birth of the user
fields.name: BIRTH_DATE

fields.description: The postal code of the account’s billing address
fields.name: ZIP

fields.description: This is the latitude of the user on sign-up. It might be updated in the future to the last seen location.
fields.name: LATITUDE

fields.description: The date the user record was created. Also referred to as the user’s "join date"
fields.name: CREATED_AT

tables.caveats: Note that employees and customer support staff will have accounts.

tables.description: Includes a catalog of all the products ever sold by the famed Sample Company.
tables.name: PRODUCTS

fields.description: The numerical product number. Only used internally. All external communication should use the title or EAN.
fields.name: ID

fields.description: The international article number. A 13 digit number uniquely identifying the product.
fields.name: EAN

fields.description: The name of the product as it should be displayed to customers.
fields.name: TITLE

fields.description: The type of product, valid values include: Doohicky, Gadget, Gizmo and Widget
fields.name: CATEGORY

fields.description: The source of the product.
fields.name: VENDOR

fields.description: The list price of the product. Note that this is not always the price the product sold for due to discounts, promotions, etc.
fields.name: PRICE

fields.description: The average rating users have given the product. This ranges from 1 - 5
fields.name: RATING

fields.description: The date the product was added to our catalog.
fields.name: CREATED_AT

tables.caveats: The rating column is an integer from 1-5 where 1 is dreadful and 5 is the best thing ever.

tables.description: Reviews that Sample Company customers have left on our products.
tables.name: REVIEWS

fields.description: A unique internal identifier for the review. Should not be used externally.
fields.name: ID

fields.description: The product the review was for
fields.name: PRODUCT_ID

target.description: The numerical product number. Only used internally. All external communication should use the title or EAN.
target.name: ID

fields.description: The user who left the review
fields.name: REVIEWER

fields.description: The rating (on a scale of 1-5) the user left.
fields.name: RATING

fields.description: The review the user left. Limited to 2000 characters.
fields.name: BODY

fields.description: The day and time a review was written by a user.
fields.name: CREATED_AT

tables.caveats: These reviews aren't tied to orders so it is possible people have reviewed products they did not purchase from us.

Metabase will cache all saved questions with an average query execution time longer than this many seconds:

To determine how long each saved question's cached result should stick around, we take the query's average execution time and multiply that by whatever you input here. So if a query takes on average 2 minutes to run, and you input 10 for your multiplier, its cache entry will persist for 20 minutes.
